        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 8:01PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 801 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Mendota to Spring Valley to near Henry.
Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of up to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
North Utica, Oglesby, Triumph, Harding, Naplate, Prairie Center,
Tonica, Leland, Mendota, Earlville, Troy Grove, La Salle, Peru, Cedar
Point, and Ottawa.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for north central
Illinois.</instruction>
